reviews.review_text: Cafe Medina! This place is so impressive! We love here. We waited the table for 35-40mins, but worth it! Also, I think they control the customer flow very well, even though they are busy, but the speed of serving food is acceptable to me. I didn t neglect the food quality just because they were busy. Highly recommend the waffle with White chocolate sauce!

FINALLY, got a chance to try this place after making reservations ($10/person booking where it gets donated).  Its nice to just walk in and not have to wait.  After taking a first bite of the waffle, I know what all the fuss is about and why its always so busy!  The food was all very delicious, our server was patient and very attentive and food was so pretty and delicious.  The ambience is cute, cozy and airy and I will 100% come back again!

Went for brunch around 11am and there was about 1hr wait but you could just leave your number and walk around downtown to explore other things until they text you. So it wasn t too bad to wait. The service was great and the steak was very tender as well! Will definitely go back and try other things!

Cafe Medina is an absolute gem! Their brunch is a delightful journey of flavors, with unique dishes that never disappoint. Must try their waffles.   The milk chocolate lavender mixed with salted caramel was our favorite topping for waffles. The atmosphere is charming. A must-visit for any foodie!

Waffles- slightly crispy with the caramelized sugar and pairs well with the pistachio rose white chocolate and berry compote (not too sweet). The paella is spicy, yummy and filling. Enough for two people. Best lavender latte Ive had! Its actually has a strong lavender flavor. Service was very efficient. We came on a Tuesday morning around 9 and got seated right away at the bar.
Really great brunch! The liege waffle with raspberry caramel is AMAZING. We also had the meatball skillet and the braised beef skillet. Seriously wow. Definitely will come back!

Not your normal breakfast place,  but thats why its great.  A little eclectic,  but nothing over the top. From the coffees, to the main courses, to the waffles at the end.  We all tried something different and they were all hits. Definitely a go to spot every time were in town.

We decided to visit this restaurant on a whim, without a reservation. Despite not having booked in advance, the friendly front desk staff still managed to accommodate us. The service was incredibly welcoming, and the meal was perfectly crafted with layers of flavor. A truly enjoyable experience!!

My first time to this great breakfast location. We ate on the patio and enjoyed the view of the revolving restaurant. The coffee and waffles didnt disappoint. I had fun with 3 different toppings and then had a side of bacon. Very yummy! My partner had the cassoulet. He loved the eggs, sausage and foccacia.

Love love love it. We waited for the place to open a bit later on a stat holiday - 9am. The staff were fast and helpful to get everyone seated. The place and atmosphere are really cozy and nice. The food is amazing! Will definitely be looking forward to try more in future visits
The food here is absolutely delicious, everything was tasty. The atmosphere is the restaurant is very pleasant and staff are friendly. There may be a slight wait time.

Great place to start your day in Vancouver. You ll probably need to wait for a while to get a table but it s worth the wait! All dishes and drinks are Moroccan inspired and there is a happy hour between 9 and 11 am which is highly recommended to try one of their delicious cocktails! Additionally, you definitely need to try one of their waffles from Liege, as a true Belgian they are really good! Vegetarian options: There are vegetarian options

Brunch vibes here are next-level, with a unique menu that adds a Middle Eastern twist! I enjoyed the boulettes dish which came with lamb meatballs & the right amount of spice -  the eggs were also perfectly poached so it was pure perfection    the fricassee came with an explosion of incredible flavours & very tender short ribs    the cozy atmosphere added that extra touch of comfort to the meal  I couldn t leave without getting their waffles which are a must-try     they re great on their own but even better with topping! I went with the milk chocolate lavender which added subtle floral notes Visited on a weekday morning & only waited about 15mins - the cozy atmosphere added that extra touch of comfort to the meal!

Great service and excellent breakfast. Shared the Fricassee, Liege waffles with mixed berry compote + maple syrup, & a side of smoked Medina bacon. I still think about this bacon. The grilled focaccia that came with the fricassee is also worth mentioning bc it s so good.  So glad we got to dine in at Cafe Medina!

The food was fresh and delicious. We were able to walk right in and be seated for a Sunday brunch. The waiter was friendly and knowledgeable of all menu items and came frequently enough to be helpful but not so much that you feel rushed. The waffles were a hit and the white chocolate pistachio sauce was one of a kind!

Came here during late lunch time but it was still packed! Thankfully I was by myself so it wasn t a long wait. FOOD was so great! I had the paella - a bit spicy (which I was notified beforehand) but overall tasted amazing.

The food was top notch! One of the best brunch I ve ever had. All the servers was super nice and our server didn t even had anything to note our order she remembered all the minor details too. Waffles are a must we ordered them twice, it can t be explained in words how good they were.
Excellent brunch option in downtown. Even on weekdays, it can be very busy with a long line for seating. For us, it was well worth the wait. Delicious and cozy brunch, great coffee, and good service.

There s always a line up to go here for brunch! Make sure you make reservations if you can and book in advance to avoid lines and disappointment!! The brunch options are different than your typical brunch place because they offer a more middle eastern flair to it with some spices, more tomato paste or something different! Their lattes are unique too and though they have their staple flavours they also offer unique ones like raspberry caramel latte or lavender hot chocolate.

Had the opportunity to pop in while travelling for work. One upside of being solo was I was seated immediately the bar. Staff were attentive, friendly and helped make recos when needed.  Stopped in for lunch so had to try a waffle with my main, and it did not dissapoint. Lavender Milk chocolate was so good drizzled on waffle I took the Fricassee Champignon which was a great lunch portion and so delicious. Eggs were cooked to perfection. To go I grabbed a lavender latte which I highly recommend.

We had to wait for 1 hour and a half to get a table, so if you want to have brunch on a weekend come early. The food was delicious, the only downside was that there was too little foccacia. Vegetarian options: There are many good vegetarian options

LOVE this place! best moka i have ever had in my life, tried different plates so here are my thoughts: the waffles are OK (the topping options are great, we ordered chocolate lavender and it   is tasty w the waffle) the mushroom dish with eggs is delicious (Fricassee Champignon)!!!! the paella (i ordered it veggie) was ok! my sister ordered tagine (veggie) and she loved it!!! will totally recommend (get early/not that hungry bc it is always packed) you can also reserve online!

My group of eight (8) out of town visitors arrived for a weekday late breakfast (9:30am) without reservations. Fortunately, we were seated immediately, so I guess we were lucky. // Cafe Medina is an unpretentious but somewhat elegant casual restaurant with a great menu. I immensely enjoyed the Fricassee  Champignons [2 sunny eggs served atop cremini & blue oyster mushrooms, king oyster mushrooms, roasted potatoes, mushroom demi glace, chevre (cheese made from goats milk), arugula & grilled focaccia]. Even though Im not a vegetarian, I have to say: Wow, what a delicious treat! And our server was super efficient & professional. If I lived in Vancouver, Id probably end up eating here again & again.

The Cafe Medina is a nice medium-sized breakfast place in downtown Vancouver. With an old-fashioned interieur reminiscent of the Belle Epoque and a modern menu, it by far exceeds the usual burger/meat heavy American breakfast restaurants you can find in larger US or Canadian cities. However, the portions are not too large, and yet the Avocado toast was delicious. The Granola was surprisingly tasteful, all fruit freshly prepared and the yoghurt tasteful. The Latte was just on-point, the Americano a little weak. The personnel is very friendly, while the short-skirt policy seems out of place and outdated. Reservations are recommended since it gets busy in the morning. Vegetarian options: Available Dietary restrictions: Everything can be adjusted Kid-friendliness: Definitely kid-friendly Wheelchair accessibility: Accessible
Excellent cafe, enjoyed our break fast. Recommend their waffles and avocado toast. The atmosphere and food both was excellent.

Cozy, vibrant, wake-me-up atmosphere at Cafe Medina pairs perfectly with the stylish, delicious food here! We came as a family and were lucky to be seated right away- service was very friendly, although there was a slight delay between our drinks and taking our order. As for the food, it was phenomenal- the wolf s breakfast to share had several sausages and sauce pairings including a lamb sausage. The potatoes and aioli were worth it alone. Highly recommend for breakfast or brunch (and possibly more!) Vegetarian options: About half of the main dishes are either vegetarian or can be made vegetarian.

Food is amazing, 5 star nailed, love their waffle and roasted potatoes, staff is super friendly and helpful, it s quite a bit of waiting though. From order to finally get our dish took like 25min, plus the walk in waiting time 25min, we have to extend our street parking to the point it is not extendable.
Lovely brunch experience, and worth the wait! We ordered the steak and eggs for 2, with 2 waffles on the side. Everything was delicious and well-portioned

The food was great, we ordered the wolf platter to share and everything was delicious. Expect to wait 1.5 hours on weekends. You can put your name/number down and then come back when you get the text.

Cafe Medina is a legit Michelin reviewed cafe with amazing and inventive breakfast and brunch. First, the coffee is outstanding living up to their credo  life to short to drink bad coffee.  The variety on the menu is amazing.  Their are traditional offerings all the way to a paella style skillet. I had the frittata of the day which was beef and potatoes.  The eggs were so fluffy and light they almost defied gravity.  The beef was well seasoned and not overly present.  We also had a special waffle with milk chocolate sauce and it did not disappoint.  There is an interesting Mediterranean flair to the brunch menu that we did not try.  Highly recco a stop here for brunch but know that you may have to wait a bit .
This place has a nice vibe. The Paella was  great. Good portion size as well. I also got the lemonade drink, which was pretty good.

Many tasty and healthy brunch items. Fricassee was delicious, the portion was also good. Waffles are fresh and warm, milk chocolate with lavender was flavorsome and totally recommended. They have various coffee based beverages, I went with classic latte. For non-coffee ones, English breakfast tea had a robust and rich flavor. The staff were nice, polite and friendly. I really liked how vibrant this place is. Making reservations is recommended, especially in weekends.

The only thing youll regret about ordering the waffles is not ordering more. Theyre great. I had two with the salted caramel and wow was it delicious. Wish they had a flight or some combo to make it easy to try out all the flavors. Guess Ill just have to come back again soon. I had the veggie harissa burger and it was quite good and filling. Overall, a great experience.

This is a great breakfast spot with yummy belgian waffles. The toppings were delicious, but I think even just the plain waffle would have been more than enough! We were worried though since we could not make a reservation, but the line was not bad when we arrived for 9am. I would definitely go again the next time Im in Vancouver!

Good place for brunch with friends. Highly recommend the Fricasse . The hot chocolate tastes fantastic and not too sweet.  The front desk assistant helped me a lot when I found that I lost my umbrella.  Its so heartwarming.

Fantastic brunch in Cafe Medina I had an amazing brunch experience with my friend in Cafe Medina. The food was delicious, the staff was attentive, and the atmosphere was pleasant. Highly recommended! Food
Worth the long waiting time. The staff are cool and their food is amazing. Love this place fr
Good food. Amazing white chocolate rose pistachio dip for my waffle!! And had a good flat white :) Hot chocolate was average, not too sweet! Food
The combination of tastes are amazing and innovative. Ive never tried something similar before. Coffee is a bit sour and could be better. We waited about 40 minutes in the line.

Cafe Medina is a Vancouver institution because it gets top marks in every category. The white chocolate/pistachio/rosewater is my go to for both coffee and waffle sauce, while the fricassee hits hard morning or afternoon. My only disappointment is that theres not a dinner service
I love the brunch options in this cafe. What I tried so far exceeded my expectations. Try to make a reservation as place is packed especially during brunch!

Wonderful spot for brunch!! Arrived on a Sunday morning not even 10 min after they opened and there was a line out the door!! We were lucky enough to get seated fairly quick.  Started with a mimosa and coffee.  For breakfast we had Saumon Fume and Avocado toast. Everything was wonderful.  Must do in Vancouver!

The service is top-class (during my stay), when I tried to order a virgin Mojito, I didn t wanted to cancel the drink and the immediate response from the bartender was to cancel the order (even though he was preparing it) and advised me to let my server know when I pay my bill. It was a very good breakfast and I hope that I will have the honour to come back and dine here again. Thank you, Cafe Medina!

We had the  Fricassee  and the  Breakfast Tajine  with two  Mimouna  (Mimosas with a little extra) Everything was delicious, tasty and freshly prepared. If you like Mediterranean-inspired cuisine, we highly recommend this brunch place.
What a nice place for brunch. Creative menu, great taste and good people. Vegetarian options: Great vegetarian options Food : 5/5 |
Very busy but for a good reason, specifically the great service and fantastic food.  Everyone enjoyed their choices, but the Les Boulettes (pictured) Moroccan meatballs was especially delicious.
Beautiful cafe with delicious food and amazing coffee. A wide selection of breakfast entrees, delicious waffles, and exquisite coffee.

A popular brunch place for good reason. We came here on a Monday at 9:45 ish for 2 and the inside tables were already full. Luckily the weather was good and we got a spot at the patio. The food is spectacular to get you a well balanced meal. I loved my paella, loads of flavor and veggies to start off my day! The waffle was also very soft and not overly sweet so you can choose how much sauce youd like to dip for yourself. The service was really great too, prompt and friendly and the entire staff considerate all around. Well deserved popularity and Id love to try more of their menu if I get the chance!

Brought my laptop with me and sat at the bar for breakfast/lunch. I ordered a platter that had a little bit of everything. egg, avocado, meat, cheese, olive spread. It was so tasty and every bite was a new adventure! The staff was super friendly. Service was quick and efficient and I would definitely go back and recommend this place:)

I am in this wonderful restaurant at the present time, here is a fantastic restaurant with awesome staff. Phil (One of the staff) suggested us caramel waffles and breakfast, we placed order exactly the same as Phil suggested us: caramel waffles for 2 times!. Phil is a very respectful person with nice voice, he has 10 star review.Definitely, I will come back again here.Jenna has a smile on her face, she is very polite and welcomed us very warmly; If I could give her ten stars, I would. I would like to update my review for my recent visit at this restaurant in July 10,2023. This afternoon, I welcomed very warmly to Cafe Medina by Charlotte (host), she is very kind and friendly lady, she seated us very quickly. Gui explained us menu in detail so that facilitated us to choose the right option in menu: Fricassee was the food that we choose. I attached a photo of Fricassee (Last Photo). Fricassee is made of braised short ribs, roasted potatoes, smoked cheddar, grilled focaccia and caramelized onions, the food was very delicious. Beautiful Aisling served us on time with smile face and in a respectful way, she is a very helpful and hardworking in serving us, she is one of the talented staff in the restaurant. In fact, I give the 5 star to all of them because of their hospitality, respectful behaviour and good advise in finding best food that match your interest. I strongly recommend this restaurant.

Worth the wait. The Wolves Breakfast was possibly the fanciest brunch I ve ever had. The coffee and espresso were great and the waffles were amazing toppings were all great but the waffle itself was awesome.

This is a very very busy spot, but very worth it. Make sure to arrive early and be prepared to wait for a while. You wont regret it. Regardless of what you order, make sure to also order one of their incredible waffles for dessert.

Love this place. Fave dishes: Les Boulettes, or daily special Frittata. Hit it every time I m in Vancouver. A touch of Paris/Brussels/ME/NAfrica/Europe on the west coast of Canada.  Decent Gluten free options incl bread. Flavours are bold and presentation is very good.  Always super staff.

Loved the waffles. They are actually great on its own. Fricassee was delicious and savoury, full of flavour. Saumon Fume tastes just like how the name is; delicious. Attentive and knowledgeable server.

Love this place! Food and service are excellent. One is due worth raising is that the chairs have rigid side rails that are restrictive to those with wide hips. Also, like many places, it s quite busy and loud. Between all the chatter and music playing, you have to raise your voice to talk across the table.
Great place for brunch. I heard the dinner menu is really good too. Good quality and tasty food with a fair price(considering the location). Overall a 4.5 star experience. Food

Really good cafe and enjoyable atmosphere, I had Couscous and it was something that I have been looking forward to figure out, healthy and delicious, which was great as you can see in the pic. Enjoyed their Medina iced tea too. Highly Recommended!

I had lunch at Medina with my mom yesterday. We had the Cassoulet and Fricassee. Thanks to Chef Trixie and her tram, the food was absolutely amazing. The restaurant atmosphere, music, and staffs are an A+. Medina is a go-to brunch spot for everyone in Vancouver. Highly recommended

The food here is amazing!  They have great waffles that I would highly recommend as a side order with one of their signature brunch items.  Their lemonade is one of the best I ve had, so if you re looking for something else to drink that s not coffee, choose that!  If you don t have a reservation that s also fine, you can give them your number and they ll tell you when to come back (there s a lot to see around the area while you wait)!

One of the best breakfasts I have EVER had. The waffles are amazing and so is the avocado toast. This place is literally always busy so make sure to get a reservation. The vibes are great and the service is also great. If you are in the neighbourhood, make sure to stop in. Also the passion fruit creme sauce is unreal and a must have.

Great place for brunch!  We came here twice during our Vancouver stay.  The foods is delicious and the service is wonderful.  Make sure you make reservation online or you might need to wait up for 90mins during holidays (yes, it s that popular )
Had the best waffles EVER! Ordered it a couple of more times as starters. Our hostess was very friendly and her recommendations were excellent! Food
Parking is not easy given it s located in Downtown, but flavor is good. I tried lamb meatballs. Plus they serve 8 oz beer, which is a great option for daytime meals.
Great food! I really enjoyed the Harrissa Burger. I recommend avoiding Cafe Medina on the weekend as its always extremely busy. Food : 5/5

Update: Cafe Medina continues to be a favourite and well worth the visit! The team is excellent, the beverages are great, and the food has satisfied every time! Having tried most of their menu, you cant really miss, but some notable favorites are the Cous Cous salad (after 11am), Le Complete, and the Paella.

We made a reservation as soon as slots were released and we were so glad we managed to give this place a try while on vacation in Vancouver. The meatballs was well-seasoned and I enjoyed my dish. The waffles are definitely a must-try with the white chocolate option. The waffles were crispy on the outside and chewy on the inside
Loved the waffle, the dipping the coffee, awesome ambience and good customer service
Nice Cafe with various dishes, perfect for breakfast. I recommend the waffles. It is very busy in the morning and loud inside, but the atmosphere is still good.
Great spot for breakfast and brunch. Wide range of dishes, well cooked and seasoned.

Best place in town for brunch! We order the lamb meatballs and the short ribs with eggs, it was so delicious. You can taste the quality of the food. Make sure to order the waffles they are perfect as dessert.

Excellent breakfast/brunch restaurant! I absolutely love their waffles with milk chocolate lavender sauce. The servers are always friendly and in a good mood and the place is bright. If youre going by yourself, there is seating at the bar. If you come with a group, expect to wait in line because this is a very popular restaurants.

It was Wednesday Brunch time, a packed restaurant with a couple of walk-in tables available.  We were seated right away without reservations or waitlisting.  Great customer service, attentive staff, great tasting dishes.  We also had the waffles (daily limited supply) paired with Milk Choc w/Lavender & White Choc Pistachio Rose-water toppings.  The WCPRw reminded us of the Indian dish, Rasmalai...
Long waits to get in at busier times but food is worth it. Coffee and food taste great!

Ah-mazing! Beautiful indoors, great service, and even better food. I had a reservation and was seated upon arrival. It was a full house during a weekday so I would definitely recommend a reservation unless you are fine with waiting an hour plus. My husband and I ordered a few things which were all delicious! 1. Latte-  loved that they put it in a small glass cup. It was really yummy and something I would order again. 2. Paella without chorizo- this was delicious. Beautiful flavors of the vegetables mixed with the orzo and a hint of lemon. I ordered the egg on the side scrambled. 3.Frittata- roasted vegetables mixed with the lightest fluffiest eggs Ive ever had. Came with a side of greens and focaccia. Both were amazing as well. 4. Roasted potatoes with lemon aioli- sooo good. I love potatoes and these hit the spot. They were not the traditional crispy breakfast potatoes. These were soft with like a light balsamic glaze and cheddar. The lemon aioli was also very good. Definitely nothing like Ive had before. 5. Liege style waffle with White Chocolate Pistachio Rosewater sauce- The waffle was really soft and sweet. The sauce for me was a miss. I thought it tasted like condensed milk. I would 100% come back here to try the different menu options! Vegetarian options: Many of the menu items can be vegetarian!

Reserve a table online if you can since the restaurant is usually busy. The waiters are friendly and the orders arrived pretty fast. The food was delicious and the atmosphere was quite comfortable. We will definitely come back to try more different dishes. Food

Excellent service. Great food with fresh ingredients! Lots of great options for vegetarians since they can make most of their dishes without meat. Loved the salted caramel latte and the lavender latte was a fun twist.  Clean baby change station in bathroom.

hearty, warm, and fantastic! The atmosphere, food, and service absolutely made the dining experience satisfying, which is something I haven t had in a long time. With the cold weather, economic situation, and world events happening now, dining out doesn t feel the same, and the food or service didn t feel deserving of the price. Today I felt content eating a wholesome meal in a lively environment and remembered what it meant to eat in a restaurant again.

Best waffles in town. Such unique flavours for dips. Also delicious coffee. I loved the seasonal frittatas as well. I appreciate that you can get a coffee while you wait for a table. Really good service overall. I highly recommend the rose water dip and chocolate lavender dip

Very nice brunch place near Vancouver downtown. Need reservations to get table at this place. Servers were very good and service was quick. Many good options for the main course dishes with good portion sizes. Many dishes could be made vegetarian. Coffee was good too. Ordered waffle for dessert and they had many options for toppings.
Very unique menu. The quality of food and service is amazing. The only problem is that usually there is a line up. Other than that 5 stars  definitely try it if you love breakfast like me

One of my favourite brunch places in the city. They plate the food very photogenically and also make it taste amazing. I liked that it was not your basic chicken and waffles brunch menu it was very unique. The waffles are a MUST have even if you just have one.

Enjoyed an amazing breakfast and happy hour mimosas. Le Complet is probably one of my favorite breakfasts in the city. The bartender didnt seem very happy to be working but I guess thats her prerogative. Everyone else was super friendly. Highly recommend this place. Michelin got it right!

We went the first time on a national holiday and it was completely packed. So the next day we went around 10am, wrote our name on the list for around 1pm and then came back and had no wait. It definitely live up to the expectations, one of the nicest places we got to eat in our trip to Canada. Would recommend.

This cafe is always booked but we managed to book a table today! The atmosphere itself is very lively and welcoming, and service is fast too. Their main plates are good, nothing too special, but what stands out are their waffles! The waffles are so fresh and taste perfect alone. You also have the choice of adding toppings for $1.50, which I think is worth it. The mixed berry compote and the milk chocolate lavender pair so nice with the waffles, but Im sure any of the other toppings are just as tasty :)

Our favorite brunch place in Vancouver this entire trip. Lovely Liege style waffles, perfect pairing with the maple syrup. We ordered Fricassee and Harissa  Burger , both are delicious and memorable, and the portions are just right. Wait time isnt too bad if you arrive early on a weekday, the line starts around 8:40/8:45AM. Reservations are recommended & you will get to skip the line and get seated prior to the folks lining up.
For a tasty and filling breakfast, Cafe Medina is a top choice. Their plates are both delicious and substantial. Highly recommend!

We picked this place because Im from Medinah, IL. Not knowing what to expect. Well, well, well were we pleased with my choice. It was very busy when we arrived and the host greeted us promptly and even offered coffee while we waited for a table. The atmosphere was a classy Cafe. The food was great! The service was efficientl and friendly.

@medinacafe     was one of the top most brunching places in Vancouver ,ticked off another Michelin star   restaurant  .The food was so good ,we could reserve and finally visit recently ...Dont miss their Liege Style Waffle    , it was an amazing   end of our brunch date. If you havent been,just go and try, they even take walk-ins,but it might  be a long wait

Such a beautiful restaurant and amazing staffs/service. We ordered the Saumon Fume and Les Boulettes and it was just the most delicious thing ever. The Saumon Fume was very lightweight, but flavorful. The Les Boulettes was definitely more filling, but the favor was immaculate. The prices were very reasonable. Definitely a wonderful place to eat and there s plenty of drink options. Totally recommend!

We had a yummy breakfast after finding this place online. I had 2 of the Liege waffles with dark chocolate sauce and a side of fresh fruit.  My husband had the Harissa burger. It was all delicious.  Our server was friendly and helpful. I didn t quite understand why it took so long for the waffles to be served.  They came several minutes after the other food and they just had to be taken out of the case. Oh well. It didn t ruin the experience.

Very popular spot that requires reservations in advance, but will not take reservations for large groups. There is a deposit fee for booking reservations that is not returned for no-shows or late cancellations. Great food that can be customized with their abundant side dish options. There is ample indoor seating and limited outdoor seating that have umbrella cover and shade from the adjacent building so you dont get too much sun.
What a beautiful unique cafe. The service was just top notch. It was super busy on a Thursday mid morning. The food was quick, fresh and tasty.

Good food. Decently priced. Expected a little more quantity. Great service. Would go again for the ambience and the taste. Second visit had the Harissa burger which was great. Their waffles are worth the price tag, and try it with the white chocolate pistachio rosewater topping.

It took about an hour after reserving a table for it to become available, but after that the staff was very attentive, the food was well made and the portions werent too big. I forgot my bag there and the staff ran after me and brought it over for me. Very thankful to them. Vegetarian options: They have a label on most food indication a vegetarian option or an adjustment which can be made

A Vancouver institution. Food is consistently good. Make sure to get the lavender latte and liege waffles for the full experience. Fricassee and Cassoulet are also stand outs but you cannot go wrong with anything. Reservations highly recommended. Edit: visited again in June 2022. Quality is still consistent and I still highly recommend.

A favorite spot for breakfast and brunch, Cafe Medina has a varying selection of delicious Mediterranean inspired dishes. My go to us the fricassee which is beautifully prepared in a skillet and features fall apart tender short ribs that are packed full of flavour. If you need a little amuse then the liege waffles are a must have. A selection of sauces blend perfectly with the flavours of the waffle. The service and attention to detail is impeccable and the art of hospitality is grade A. There are multiple touch points to make sure things are right for you but not too much to make it seem like they are hovering. Highly recommend while you can to book a table as lines typically start pre-opening all days of the week. Update. We continue to go here and the food continues to amaze and be consistently delicious.

Medina is Vancouvers best brunch. They dont take reservations, so if you dont want to wait in a long line, I recommend only visiting on weekdays or trying to get there for when they open. The wolfs breakfast is amazing, and I also loved the flat bread. You must try the waffles with some of the amazingly unique sauces they make in house as well. Even though the restaurant is always packed, service has always been excellent as well. Update: recently returned and tried the Le Complet, which was also awesome! We also had the please of being served by Jeffery who provided some of the most polite and expedient service I have experienced anywhere.

My go-to brunch spot every time I pass by Vancouver! There was a short wait to get in when we arrived 5 min before opening, but we managed to get a table for 2 without reservations on Easter Monday. The Fricasse was to die for, the braised ribs fork tender (and who doesn t want to eat out of a skillet?) We also shared a couple of their famous waffles, the passion fruit curd came highly recommended by our waitress. It was so good that we ended up getting more waffles because we didn t want to waste it.

Absolutely amazing. Great food, attentive service, and a bustling ambience. The paella was delicious with chunks of sausage and vegetables. The avocados were a great addition. The fricassee was even better, with a sweet tomato base to dip the bread in. The short ribs were very tender and well seasoned. Lastly, we had a waffle with white chocolate pistachio rosewater. Unfortunately, I didnt get much white chocolate flavour out of this - it seemed closer to condensed milk. Nevertheless, it was still very good.

Absolutely fantastic dining experience. We went for a late breakfast. The quality of food was incredible and the service matched it! Pretty busy but they seem to get through the lineup quickly. I d certainly recommend visiting here.
